01:01:35,958 --> 01:01:38,017
but he stopped me from seeing her.

532
01:01:38,161 --> 01:01:40,891
I think he's mad at Mr. Rose.

533
01:01:41,531 --> 01:01:44,261
We were very close.

534
01:01:48,604 --> 01:01:51,801
He doesn't think he's sick.

535
01:01:52,709 --> 01:01:56,440
He says it's a plot.

536
01:01:56,579 --> 01:02:01,107
In your profession,
you call it paranoia, don't you?

537
01:02:01,250 --> 01:02:08,452
Unless it really is a plot,
then why won't he talk about it?

538
01:02:08,591 --> 01:02:12,789
Can you help me
to understand my husband?

539
01:02:15,231 --> 01:02:17,131
What could I say?

540
01:02:17,266 --> 01:02:20,429
I promised to stay in contact,

541
01:02:20,570 --> 01:02:24,597
and see her husband
before reaching a conclusion.

542
01:02:24,741 --> 01:02:26,208
She seemed relieved

543
01:02:26,342 --> 01:02:27,969
and watched from the front door

544
01:02:28,111 --> 01:02:31,877
until my car disappeared
around the corner.

545
01:02:38,921 --> 01:02:46,054
I thought we might
move the guy in product supply.

546
01:02:46,195 --> 01:02:49,494
Yeah, that's it, Daragon.

547
01:02:50,099 --> 01:02:55,628
And maybe put him
in product improvement

548
01:02:55,772 --> 01:02:58,900
until Wednesday, or something.

549
01:02:59,041 --> 01:03:01,100
Until he comes back.

550
01:03:01,844 --> 01:03:06,838
I don't know.
I'll call you back.

551
01:03:06,983 --> 01:03:09,611
Isabelle, do you want some coffee?

552
01:03:22,532 --> 01:03:24,796
Shut up! I don't know you, asshole!

553
01:03:24,934 --> 01:03:27,095
What's wrong?

554
01:03:27,236 --> 01:03:28,635
Let go of me!

555
01:03:28,771 --> 01:03:31,365
-You were at the rave on Saturday?
-Yes.

556
01:03:31,507 --> 01:03:33,566
You were fighting with a girl, right?

557
01:03:33,709 --> 01:03:35,643
What girl?

558
01:03:35,778 --> 01:03:37,643
"Shut up! I don't know you, bitch!"

559
01:03:37,780 --> 01:03:39,179
Remember?

560
01:03:39,315 --> 01:03:40,646
No.

561
01:03:40,783 --> 01:03:42,148
No, nothing.

562
01:03:42,285 --> 01:03:45,220
I didn't say that to you!

563
01:03:45,655 --> 01:03:46,952
Wait! Tell me....

564
01:04:33,703 --> 01:04:35,136
Yes?

565
01:04:38,307 --> 01:04:40,366
I was just leaving.

566
01:04:45,014 --> 01:04:46,504
Fine.

567
01:05:12,008 --> 01:05:14,670
The business world unforgiving.

568
01:05:16,812 --> 01:05:20,976
How do you reconcile
"the human factor"

569
01:05:21,117 --> 01:05:25,076
with the company's need
to make money?

570
01:05:26,555 --> 01:05:31,754
How did you cope
with the restructuring process?

571
01:05:31,894 --> 01:05:36,627
I was only indirectly involved.

572
01:05:36,766 --> 01:05:39,166
Don't be so modest.

573
01:05:39,302 --> 01:05:45,070
You played a major role
in the decision-making process.

574
01:05:45,207 --> 01:05:47,175
Yes, I was there.

575
01:05:47,310 --> 01:05:51,269
But you made the project a success.

576
01:05:51,414 --> 01:05:54,713
You were the one behind it.

577
01:05:54,850 --> 01:06:00,584
Thanks to your dynamic
collaboration.

578
01:06:03,092 --> 01:06:13,661
I asked you to refine
the employee evaluation criteria.

579
01:06:13,803 --> 01:06:18,069
You really gave us your all.

580
01:06:18,708 --> 01:06:25,773
We went from 2,500 units to 1,200.

581
01:06:25,915 --> 01:06:27,712
We recovered our shareholders.

582
01:06:27,917 --> 01:06:31,910
It was a huge success!

583
01:06:36,792 --> 01:06:41,286
The quality of the files you presented
was most impressive.

584
01:06:42,365 --> 01:06:46,495
You know exactly
how to define selection criteria

585
01:06:46,635 --> 01:06:50,264
according to the company's needs.

586
01:06:51,040 --> 01:06:56,103
That's your strength, Mr. Kessler.

587
01:06:59,782 --> 01:07:04,947
I've never hesitated to hire
a candidate you put forward.

588
01:07:05,087 --> 01:07:08,284
And I've never had cause to regret it.

589
01:07:08,924 --> 01:07:14,726
Unfortunately,
others have made mistakes

590
01:07:14,864 --> 01:07:17,765
which have caused us
serious financial damage.

591
01:07:17,900 --> 01:07:21,336
It's their loss, too.
Recruitment costs money.

592
01:07:21,470 --> 01:07:24,462
One has to accept
one's responsibilities.

593
01:07:25,141 --> 01:07:28,872
I pay them to choose
the right people.

594
01:07:40,589 --> 01:07:44,548
Today, there's not one alcoholic
left in the factory.

595
01:07:45,461 --> 01:07:49,795
Before restructuring
we created special jobs for them

596
01:07:49,932 --> 01:07:52,628
to be "charitable".

597
01:07:58,340 --> 01:08:01,434
You had no qualms
about laying people off.

598
01:08:01,577 --> 01:08:05,343
They gave us real safety problems
in some areas.

599
01:08:05,481 --> 01:08:07,574
Of course.

600
01:08:07,716 --> 01:08:14,144
You didn't give an inch
when the unions tried to intervene.

601
01:08:15,024 --> 01:08:16,753
You stood your ground.

602
01:08:16,892 --> 01:08:20,692
They didn't know the risk
we were running.

603
01:08:20,830 --> 01:08:22,525
Keeping on sick workers.

604
01:08:22,665 --> 01:08:25,293
AIcoholism is a sickness.

605
01:08:25,501 --> 01:08:29,699
They'd be incapable of responding
to an emergency.

606
01:08:29,839 --> 01:08:35,106
Imagine a vital pump breaking.

607
01:08:35,244 --> 01:08:36,871
You have to react immediately.

608
01:08:37,012 --> 01:08:41,346
There's no room for error.
The workshops are dangerous.

609
01:08:41,484 --> 01:08:44,976
There's gas, hydrogen.
Disaster is always looming.

610
01:08:45,121 --> 01:08:47,521
Safety regulations were ignored.

611
01:08:47,656 --> 01:08:50,386
I've seen "specialists"
handling toxic products

612
01:08:50,593 --> 01:08:52,220
without gloves or masks.

613
01:08:52,361 --> 01:08:56,297
We've got hydrogen sulphide,
nitrogen oxide, phenol.

614
01:08:56,432 --> 01:08:58,798
Take your pick!

615
01:08:58,934 --> 01:09:01,835
And they blame it
on staff shortages.

616
01:09:02,037 --> 01:09:02,731
Crap!

617
01:09:02,872 --> 01:09:07,775
I just couldn't let it go,
for their safety and for ours.

618
01:09:07,910 --> 01:09:10,174
And you were right!

619
01:09:30,766 --> 01:09:35,430
I never noticed you worked
outside office hours.

620
01:09:40,209 --> 01:09:46,842
I'm well aware that Karl Rose
told you to keep an eye on me.

621
01:09:47,049 --> 01:09:50,985
He gave you this task.

622
01:09:52,788 --> 01:09:56,417
He's turning my own people
against me.

623
01:09:58,194 --> 01:10:02,221
Karl Rose has decided
to undermine me.

624
01:10:03,766 --> 01:10:04,790
If he wants to get rid of me

625
01:10:04,934 --> 01:10:12,067
it's because he knows
I've got some extremely serious,

626
01:10:12,208 --> 01:10:17,305
confidential, and compromising
information.

627
01:10:19,415 --> 01:10:26,947
Karl Rose used to be known
as Karl Kraus.

628
01:10:27,423 --> 01:10:36,764
In 1 936, Heinrich Himmler
founded the Lebensborn movement,

629
01:10:36,899 --> 01:10:41,461
literally, "source of life",

630
01:10:41,670 --> 01:10:46,869
gathering from shelters
and maternity wards Aryan children,

631
01:10:47,009 --> 01:10:50,410
many of whom were orphans.

632
01:10:50,546 --> 01:10:52,104
By the end of the war,

633
01:10:52,248 --> 01:10:55,081
these children had been adopted
by German families,

634
01:10:55,217 --> 01:10:57,117
which was the case of Karl Rose.

635
01:10:57,319 --> 01:11:00,345
He is a "Lebensborn child".

636
01:11:00,489 --> 01:11:02,980
It obviously isn't his fault.

637
01:11:04,760 --> 01:11:10,130
He grew up in a family nostalgic
for the Schwarzen Orden,

638
01:11:10,266 --> 01:11:12,791
and maintained dubious links

639
01:11:12,935 --> 01:11:17,372
with people sharing
the same ideology.

640
01:11:17,506 --> 01:11:20,805
I have concrete proof of this.

641
01:11:21,677 --> 01:11:24,612
He sent donations
to a bogus company,

642
01:11:24,747 --> 01:11:29,912
which passed them on
to an extreme right-wing group,

643
01:11:30,052 --> 01:11:36,821
which had its own paramilitary cell.

644
01:11:37,026 --> 01:11:41,156
I have all this information
at my disposal.

645
01:11:44,600 --> 01:11:47,125
Do you understand now?

646
01:12:00,949 --> 01:12:03,918
Now you can do as you like.

647
01:12:05,354 --> 01:12:08,289
I've said everything I have to say.

648
01:12:11,760 --> 01:12:16,891
How's your little orchestra going?

649
01:12:56,805 --> 01:12:59,865
-Did I scare you?
-No.

650
01:13:58,167 --> 01:13:59,725
Where are you going?

651
01:14:29,031 --> 01:14:30,692
What's wrong?

652
01:14:33,268 --> 01:14:35,361
What's going on?

653
01:14:39,041 --> 01:14:40,872
What's happening?

654
01:14:41,009 --> 01:14:43,409
-Stop it!
-What?

655
01:14:46,482 --> 01:14:48,746
My lover is a madman.

656
01:14:48,884 --> 01:14:50,374
Look.

657
01:14:50,519 --> 01:14:53,420
You're cold.
Dark as a prison.

658
01:14:54,890 --> 01:14:57,051
Yes, now I'm scared.

659
01:15:03,365 --> 01:15:07,961
The letter Rose sent me
filled me with unhealthy curiosity.

660
01:15:08,871 --> 01:15:13,308
It looked like an ordinary
technical report,

661
01:15:13,509 --> 01:15:16,967
full of production figures
and staff data.

662
01:15:17,112 --> 01:15:20,377
Rose wanted to draw my attention
to the differences

663
01:15:20,516 --> 01:15:23,883
between the version
written in German by Jüst

664
01:15:24,019 --> 01:15:27,546
and the typed copy
obviously corrected by his secretary,

665
01:15:27,689 --> 01:15:29,452
Lynn Sanderson.

666
01:15:31,960 --> 01:15:33,791
Concern.

667
01:15:36,398 --> 01:15:37,956
Selection.

668
01:15:40,269 --> 01:15:42,328
Reintegration.

669
01:15:48,277 --> 01:15:50,837
Restructuring plan.

670
01:15:51,980 --> 01:15:53,811
Relocation.

671
01:15:59,087 --> 01:16:01,282
Concern.

672
01:16:01,423 --> 01:16:03,220
Selection.

673
01:16:04,459 --> 01:16:06,484
Reintegration.

674
01:16:07,329 --> 01:16:09,854
Restructuring plan.

675
01:16:10,732 --> 01:16:12,495
Relocation.

676
01:16:15,604 --> 01:16:17,765
Reading the handwritten letter again,

677
01:16:17,906 --> 01:16:21,535
I noticed that it was
full of missing words,

678
01:16:21,677 --> 01:16:26,341
as if Jüst's mind
contained a censoring device

679
01:16:26,481 --> 01:16:27,675
like a computer virus,

680
01:16:27,816 --> 01:16:33,379
deleting certain words
and leaving blanks,

681
01:16:33,522 --> 01:16:39,017
as if they belonged
to a forbidden, secret language.

682
01:16:54,610 --> 01:16:59,104
One morning I was struggling
to complete a routine selection file.

683
01:16:59,247 --> 01:17:01,511
It was the first time
I'd felt distaste,

684
01:17:01,650 --> 01:17:04,517
even disgust for my job.

685
01:17:05,120 --> 01:17:08,317
I called in sick with the flu.

686
01:17:09,424 --> 01:17:12,655
Jüst's report is due
at the end of the week,

687
01:17:12,861 --> 01:17:14,590
but I can't write a word.

688
01:17:14,730 --> 01:17:22,967
I'm going to make a hole.

689
01:17:23,105 --> 01:17:24,732
I need your cigarette.

690
01:17:24,873 --> 01:17:25,840
What?

691
01:17:26,441 --> 01:17:28,375
Don't move.

692
01:17:30,512 --> 01:17:31,877
I let it burn.

693
01:17:33,281 --> 01:17:35,408
I push it well in.

694
01:17:56,538 --> 01:17:58,165
Do it again.

695
01:18:00,776 --> 01:18:03,267
Annoying, isn't it?

696
01:18:09,718 --> 01:18:12,551
Usually I only do it once.

697
01:18:13,488 --> 01:18:15,854
Is it lit?

698
01:18:15,991 --> 01:18:18,789
You're trying it on the cashmere?

699
01:18:21,229 --> 01:18:23,663
Cashmere burns well.

700
01:18:29,237 --> 01:18:32,070
It works the same way.

701
01:18:33,375 --> 01:18:35,240
Don't move.

702
01:18:59,935 --> 01:19:01,994
Oh, what's going on?

703
01:19:18,053 --> 01:19:19,350
I'll give you another one.

704
01:19:22,557 --> 01:19:24,024
Good evening, gentlemen. Police!

705
01:19:24,159 --> 01:19:26,650
Hands on the table!
Stop playing, please.

706
01:19:26,795 --> 01:19:29,229
What did we do?

707
01:20:56,287 --> 01:20:57,720
Mathias!

708
01:21:39,897 --> 01:21:43,298
This accident
has really shaken me up.

709
01:21:43,868 --> 01:21:46,359
Have you spoken to the doctors?

710
01:21:46,504 --> 01:21:47,971
Yes, of course.

711
01:21:48,106 --> 01:21:49,596
But they were very discreet.

712
01:21:49,740 --> 01:21:51,765
I didn't find out much.

713
01:21:52,910 --> 01:21:55,105
And Mrs. Jüst?

714
01:21:55,646 --> 01:21:58,444
She says her husband
is very sensitive.

715
01:21:58,583 --> 01:22:04,078
Since their child's death,
he's had bouts of severe sadness.

716
01:22:04,222 --> 01:22:06,156
Of course.

717
01:22:06,290 --> 01:22:11,592
You could have tried harder
to find out what really happened.

718
01:22:11,729 --> 01:22:16,792
Mrs. Jüst was very distressed.
I didn't want to press her further.

719
01:22:18,269 --> 01:22:24,139
Before this incident, what was
your clinical opinion of him?

720
01:22:24,275 --> 01:22:26,266
He's difficult to read.

721
01:22:26,410 --> 01:22:29,641
He's highly principled
with a strong sense of duty.

722
01:22:29,780 --> 01:22:32,374
A workaholic with a one track mind.

723
01:22:32,517 --> 01:22:35,008
He's suffering from exhaustion.

724
01:22:35,153 --> 01:22:37,053
Despite his hard exterior,

725
01:22:37,188 --> 01:22:41,454
he seems very sensitive
to what he calls the "human question".

726
01:22:42,460 --> 01:22:44,792
Where did you meet?

727
01:22:44,929 --> 01:22:46,920
Here, in his office.

728
01:22:47,064 --> 01:22:49,794
-How many times?
-Twice.

729
01:22:50,001 --> 01:22:52,469
You mentioned a third meeting
just now.

730
01:22:53,104 --> 01:22:55,436
The first time was over the phone.

731
01:22:55,573 --> 01:23:00,169
As I said, I tried to find out more,
to ask more personal questions,

732
01:23:00,311 --> 01:23:01,505
but without success.

733
01:23:01,646 --> 01:23:02,738
He is very wary.

734
01:23:02,947 --> 01:23:05,279
You mean, he's paranoid?

735
01:23:05,416 --> 01:23:10,285
No, I meant his irascible nature

736
01:23:10,421 --> 01:23:12,514
makes it hard for him
to confide in people.

737
01:23:12,723 --> 01:23:16,352
He's just going through a hard time.

738
01:23:16,494 --> 01:23:20,191
He's got worries that might lead
to a personal crisis.

739
01:23:20,331 --> 01:23:22,561
The kind we've all been through.

740
01:23:22,767 --> 01:23:26,635
What do you mean,
"the kind we've all been through"?

741
01:23:26,771 --> 01:23:31,208
It's a phase more than a crisis.

742
01:23:31,409 --> 01:23:33,001
It's not depression.

743
01:23:33,144 --> 01:23:36,272
An ordeal.
That's a better way of putting it.

744
01:23:36,514 --> 01:23:37,640
Wait a minute.

745
01:23:37,782 --> 01:23:40,046
Is it a crisis or not?

746
01:23:40,618 --> 01:23:42,245
Depression or not?

747
01:23:43,821 --> 01:23:46,722
You mentioned exhaustion.
What kind?

748
01:23:47,892 --> 01:23:49,484
That's the impression I got.

749
01:23:49,627 --> 01:23:53,358
Maybe he just needs a vacation.

750
01:23:53,564 --> 01:23:59,161
There's a difference between clinical
exhaustion and needing a break.

751
01:24:01,405 --> 01:24:03,532
And his secretary?

752
01:24:06,811 --> 01:24:09,507
She doesn't think there's a problem.

753
01:24:11,382 --> 01:24:13,350
You must be joking!

754
01:24:14,185 --> 01:24:17,848
She's the one who first alerted me.

755
01:24:17,989 --> 01:24:21,254
She spoke of a breakdown,
depression,

756
01:24:21,392 --> 01:24:23,917
discrepancies in his work.

757
01:24:24,962 --> 01:24:29,763
If I brought you in,
it was to report on his mental decay.

758
01:24:29,967 --> 01:24:32,435
To be honest,

759
01:24:32,570 --> 01:24:38,440
this assignment
is causing me great distress.

760
01:24:38,576 --> 01:24:41,545
What's making you pull back?

761
01:24:41,679 --> 01:24:45,843
What are you keeping from me?
I want to know everything.

762
01:24:45,983 --> 01:24:47,245
Everything is in the file.

763
01:24:47,385 --> 01:24:50,354
You're contradicting yourself,
playing dumb and avoiding questions.

764
01:24:50,488 --> 01:24:53,457
I think the man's just tired.

765
01:24:53,591 --> 01:24:55,058
You're Iying.

766
01:24:55,192 --> 01:24:56,989
You lied about seeing him.

767
01:24:57,194 --> 01:25:00,163
-When?
-I know you saw him at his house.

768
01:25:00,298 --> 01:25:04,928
- I needed a clearer picture of him.
-What happened?

769
01:25:06,337 --> 01:25:08,430
Nothing. I just gave him a file.

770
01:25:08,572 --> 01:25:10,403
I don't understand your distress.

771
01:25:10,541 --> 01:25:13,567
You're not making yourself clear.

772
01:25:13,778 --> 01:25:16,440
By calling
a "personal crisis" a "phase",

773
01:25:16,580 --> 01:25:19,845
you're either trying
to create a smoke screen

774
01:25:19,984 --> 01:25:24,387
or deliberately misleading me
with unrelated facts.

775
01:25:25,890 --> 01:25:28,984
I think I was wrong
in coming to you.

776
01:25:29,126 --> 01:25:33,119
I overestimated
your professional abilities.

777
01:25:33,264 --> 01:25:37,496
You're a dutiful subaltern
but you lack imagination.

778
01:25:43,541 --> 01:25:47,307
For a moment,
I saw him as Jüst had:

779
01:25:47,445 --> 01:25:49,970
Karl Kraus,
child of the Schwarzen Orden,

780
01:25:50,181 --> 01:25:51,773
nobody's child,

781
01:25:51,916 --> 01:25:54,680
one of another breed of children,

782
01:25:54,819 --> 01:25:56,912
all perfect and alike.

783
01:25:57,054 --> 01:26:01,320
A child with no childhood,
no heart, no soul, no descendants.

784
01:26:01,525 --> 01:26:04,653
A child from the new, pure,
technical generation.

785
01:26:23,814 --> 01:26:27,807
For over a year, Karl Rose
has been blackmailing me.

786
01:26:27,952 --> 01:26:31,251
I couldn't stand it anymore.
I betrayed Mathias.

787
01:26:31,389 --> 01:26:36,986
I was afraid of reprisals
and his state of health scared me.

788
01:26:41,432 --> 01:26:44,765
It's kind of you
to have come so quickly.

789
01:26:44,902 --> 01:26:48,531
You sounded worried on the phone.

790
01:26:51,876 --> 01:26:57,371
I was Mathias' girlfriend
at the time of the Quartet.

791
01:26:57,515 --> 01:26:59,142
We grew apart

792
