used for that many.

892
01:34:53,690 --> 01:34:55,521
The problem is not
one of overloading,

893
01:34:55,659 --> 01:35:02,155
but the effect of maximum loading
on the vehicle's maneuverability.

894
01:35:02,299 --> 01:35:03,857
It therefore seems necessary

895
01:35:04,001 --> 01:35:06,970
to reduce the cargo area
by one meter.

896
01:35:07,104 --> 01:35:09,902
Reducing the number of pieces
as we've been doing

897
01:35:10,040 --> 01:35:11,632
is not the answer

898
01:35:11,775 --> 01:35:15,768
because the empty space must also
be filled with carbon monoxide.

899
01:35:21,985 --> 01:35:25,978
The manufacturer pointed out

900
01:35:26,123 --> 01:35:29,820
that making the van shorter
at the rear

901
01:35:29,960 --> 01:35:34,090
would cause the cargo
to shift towards the front,

902
01:35:34,231 --> 01:35:36,597
and might overload the axle.

903
01:35:36,733 --> 01:35:38,633
In fact,

904
01:35:38,769 --> 01:35:44,366
there is a natural compensation
in the distribution of the load.

905
01:35:47,144 --> 01:35:49,612
There is a natural compensation
in the distribution of the load

906
01:35:49,746 --> 01:35:53,409
