01:50:45,174 --> 01:50:50,009
"Any element unfit for work
will be dealt with accordingly

1046
01:50:50,146 --> 01:50:55,448
in line with the objective criteria
as one deals with a sick limb.

1047
01:50:55,585 --> 01:50:57,951
We'll bear in mind items such as:

1048
01:50:58,087 --> 01:50:59,213
1. Age.

1049
01:50:59,355 --> 01:51:00,982
2. Absenteeism.

1050
01:51:01,123 --> 01:51:05,355
3. Adaptability
according to ability/convertibility

1051
01:51:05,494 --> 01:51:09,328
not forgetting the regularly
updated evaluation codes.

1052
01:51:09,465 --> 01:51:12,957
It must be remembered
that faulty individuals

1053
01:51:13,102 --> 01:51:19,940
may have a negative influence
on their successors.

1054
01:51:20,443 --> 01:51:25,039
Security checks will employ
modern electronic technology

1055
01:51:25,181 --> 01:51:33,213
to detect stowaways and other
undesirable elements in the vans

1056
01:51:33,356 --> 01:51:40,023
by picking up carbon gas emissions
in the breath.

1057
01:51:40,630 --> 01:51:48,503
We've recently installed
heart-beat detectors,

1058
01:51:48,638 --> 01:51:50,765
which are more efficient,

1059
01:51:50,907 --> 01:51:56,470
and enable us
to detect signs of life.

1060
01:51:58,381 --> 01:52:02,147
The device will examine
each vehicle.

1061
01:52:02,285 --> 01:52:05,550
No one can escape it.

1062
01:52:06,589 --> 01:52:10,753
7,000 have been picked up
since the beginning of the year.

1063
01:52:12,228 --> 01:52:16,460
The engineers are pleased
with their results.

1064
01:52:20,403 --> 01:52:23,839
We used to arrest 230 per day.

1065
01:52:23,973 --> 01:52:26,498
This figure has now dropped
to 160 a month,

1066
01:52:26,642 --> 01:52:32,239
thanks to increased Franco-British
collaboration in this field.

1067
01:52:33,683 --> 01:52:37,983
Our operation
will progressively spread

1068
01:52:38,120 --> 01:52:44,150
to all French and English ports
affected by the same problems."

1069
01:52:52,835 --> 01:52:57,272
I found this article in a daily paper
from February 2006.

1070
01:55:08,237 --> 01:55:10,899
Here you are.
Enjoy your meal.

1071
01:55:11,040 --> 01:55:12,667
Thank you.

1072
01:55:13,709 --> 01:55:15,836
A beer, please.

1073
01:55:49,278 --> 01:55:52,475
-News from Patrice?
-He got attacked.

1074
01:55:52,615 --> 01:55:55,311
-And?
-He's going to report it.

1075
01:55:55,451 --> 01:55:57,009
He's right.

1076
01:56:07,296 --> 01:56:08,991
Good-bye.

1077
01:56:45,901 --> 01:56:48,062
What's wrong with him?

1078
01:56:48,204 --> 01:56:51,105
Bladder stones.
It's something cats get.

1079
01:56:51,240 --> 01:56:54,676
Couldn't you have prevented it?

1080
01:56:54,810 --> 01:56:57,472
No, you can't do much about it.

1081
01:56:57,613 --> 01:56:59,979
AImost all cats get them.

1082
01:57:00,115 --> 01:57:02,083
I know, but....

1083
01:57:02,218 --> 01:57:05,119
After a certain age,
it's bound to happen.

1084
01:57:05,254 --> 01:57:07,848
Give him a little kiss from me, okay?

1085
01:57:08,057 --> 01:57:11,515
I always get "Kimsala" and "Kimsal"
mixed up.

1086
01:57:11,660 --> 01:57:13,287
It's Timsal.

1087
01:57:13,429 --> 01:57:15,397
I always get it wrong.

1088
01:57:15,531 --> 01:57:17,658
I say it every morning.

1089
01:57:17,800 --> 01:57:19,700
It's crazy!

1090
01:57:19,835 --> 01:57:22,201
Did he say it was serious?

1091
01:57:22,404 --> 01:57:24,736
It happens to cats when they're nine.

1092
01:57:24,873 --> 01:57:27,865
I know. Just give him
a little kiss for me.

1093
01:57:28,010 --> 01:57:30,342
Another coffee, please.

1094
01:57:30,479 --> 01:57:32,538
-It's been ages.
-I'll give him a hug.

1095
01:57:32,681 --> 01:57:34,581
Even if it's a cat, we don't care.

1096
01:57:34,717 --> 01:57:37,481
I promise I'll give him a cuddle.

1097
01:57:37,620 --> 01:57:41,283
-He'll be happy.
-I'm going over there.

1098
01:57:41,423 --> 01:57:44,950
Don't forget your knife.

1099
01:57:48,030 --> 01:57:49,588
Thank you.

1100
01:57:58,741 --> 01:58:01,005
-Hello.
-Hi, Philippe. How are you?

1101
01:58:01,977 --> 01:58:04,036
Arie Neumann?

1102
01:58:04,179 --> 01:58:06,044
Yes, that's me.

1103
01:58:07,182 --> 01:58:09,412
You wrote to me.

1104
01:58:10,786 --> 01:58:12,276
Sit down.

1105
01:58:16,191 --> 01:58:19,592
It's cowardly to send letters
without signing them.

1106
01:58:20,596 --> 01:58:22,496
Why did you come to see me?

1107
01:58:22,631 --> 01:58:25,759
Your last letter
was particularly insulting.

1108
01:58:25,901 --> 01:58:27,562
You could have ignored it.

1109
01:58:27,703 --> 01:58:31,503
You could have just burned it.

1110
01:58:31,640 --> 01:58:33,699
Maybe.

1111
01:58:33,842 --> 01:58:37,005
But I wanted to see your face.

1112
01:58:37,212 --> 01:58:40,113
Each one of these texts is signed,

1113
01:58:40,249 --> 01:58:44,652
with a name or by the system
that produced them.

1114
01:58:48,824 --> 01:58:52,157
It's perverse to hide like this.

1115
01:58:52,294 --> 01:58:54,125
It's not human.

1116
01:58:54,330 --> 01:58:55,888
You're right.

1117
01:58:57,266 --> 01:59:02,294
Those are the exact words:
"not human."

1118
01:59:04,440 --> 01:59:06,601
A gratuitous play on Jüst's name.

1119
01:59:06,742 --> 01:59:12,180
A play on a name,
one word for another.

1120
01:59:12,381 --> 01:59:14,144
A resemblance.

1121
01:59:14,283 --> 01:59:17,377
It's so common these days.

1122
01:59:17,519 --> 01:59:23,287
Language is a powerful means
of propaganda.

1123
01:59:24,460 --> 01:59:27,896
It's the most public
and the most secret

1124
01:59:28,030 --> 01:59:30,055
at the same time.

1125
01:59:30,199 --> 01:59:32,133
The effect of this propaganda

1126
01:59:32,267 --> 01:59:40,538
isn't produced by speeches,
articles, and flyers.

1127
01:59:40,676 --> 01:59:46,046
It seeps into the masses'
flesh and blood.

1128
01:59:46,181 --> 01:59:51,175
Did you know we don't have
poor people anymore?

1129
01:59:51,320 --> 01:59:53,948
Only people on modest incomes.

1130
01:59:54,156 --> 02:00:03,087
We no longer talk of "issues"
such as "social issues",

1131
02:00:03,232 --> 02:00:06,861
but "problems" that our specialists

1132
02:00:07,035 --> 02:00:12,098
split up into a series
of technical details.

1133
02:00:13,409 --> 02:00:19,143
For each one,
they'll find the optimum solution.

1134
02:00:20,315 --> 02:00:22,112
Efficient methods.

1135
02:00:22,251 --> 02:00:23,650
But....

1136
02:00:23,852 --> 02:00:28,312
But words emptied of all meaning.

1137
02:00:29,057 --> 02:00:32,857
It's a break down of the language.

1138
02:00:33,061 --> 02:00:36,360
A dead language.

1139
02:00:36,498 --> 02:00:38,625
Neutral.

1140
02:00:40,035 --> 02:00:43,129
Invaded by technical words.

1141
02:00:45,407 --> 02:00:51,937
A language which gradually
absorbs its humanity.

1142
02:00:52,080 --> 02:00:54,139
Understand?

1143
02:00:56,485 --> 02:01:00,182
I see a gray truck crossing the city.

1144
02:01:01,190 --> 02:01:05,354
It's an ordinary steel panel truck

1145
02:01:05,494 --> 02:01:09,863
heading towards the mines,

1146
02:01:10,999 --> 02:01:15,561
two or three kilometers
from the last houses.

1147
02:01:16,138 --> 02:01:20,006
Neither the driver
nor the escorting officer

1148
02:01:20,142 --> 02:01:23,942
look back through the observation
window into the truck.

1149
02:01:24,079 --> 02:01:25,910
They're tired.

1150
02:01:26,048 --> 02:01:32,886
They've still got 10 transports
before night falls.

1151
02:01:33,088 --> 02:01:40,392
10 journeys across town
in difficult conditions.

1152
02:01:40,529 --> 02:01:42,861
All the more difficult

1153
02:01:42,998 --> 02:01:49,096
because in the first few minutes
of the transport,

1154
02:01:49,238 --> 02:01:53,971
they have to run the engine
at full throttle

1155
02:01:54,109 --> 02:01:59,672
to drown out the screams
and the strange lurches and jolts

1156
02:01:59,815 --> 02:02:03,307
that almost make the truck
topple over.

1157
02:02:03,986 --> 02:02:07,251
Fortunately,
things soon go quiet again,

1158
02:02:07,389 --> 02:02:12,156
and the transport
is always completed on time,

1159
02:02:12,294 --> 02:02:14,592
in keeping with the schedule.

1160
02:02:16,098 --> 02:02:18,464
"Where do the trucks go?",

1161
02:02:18,600 --> 02:02:22,593
asks the child
standing at the window.

1162
02:02:22,738 --> 02:02:25,502
At nightfall,

1163
02:02:25,641 --> 02:02:30,772
the child sees the vehicles
lined up in the schoolyard.

1164
02:02:30,913 --> 02:02:37,910
He sees the drivers handing around
a bottle of Schnapps.

1165
02:02:38,053 --> 02:02:43,650
The men are exhausted,
happy to end a day

1166
02:02:43,792 --> 02:02:51,130
which began, like the others,
much too early.

1167
02:02:52,601 --> 02:02:59,769
The escorts finish off
writing up their figures

1168
02:02:59,908 --> 02:03:06,143
and hand in their daily reports.

1169
02:03:08,517 --> 02:03:13,978
The child sees his father,

1170
02:03:16,191 --> 02:03:17,624
the officer-foreman,

1171
02:03:17,759 --> 02:03:21,490
slap each man on the back,

1172
02:03:21,697 --> 02:03:24,928
and joke with each in turn.

1173
02:03:27,769 --> 02:03:33,571
The officer thinks
that if the weather's fine

1174
02:03:34,943 --> 02:03:38,743
and there's no rain
to bog down the trucks,

1175
02:03:38,880 --> 02:03:43,078
he might be able
to finish his mission

1176
02:03:43,218 --> 02:03:45,618
by the end of the week.

1177
02:03:45,754 --> 02:03:49,850
And his superior,
the Obersturmbannfürher

1178
02:03:50,726 --> 02:03:57,359
who issued the order
from a place 100 kilometers away,

1179
02:03:57,499 --> 02:03:59,296
will congratulate him

1180
02:03:59,434 --> 02:04:03,302
on the smooth-running
of the operation.

1181
02:04:03,438 --> 02:04:11,209
If you were to ask each man
what he was doing,

1182
02:04:12,280 --> 02:04:15,181
he would reply,

1183
02:04:15,317 --> 02:04:17,877
"Everything's going as planned,

1184
02:04:19,955 --> 02:04:25,860
although it's possible
we're a little behind schedule."

1185
02:04:28,363 --> 02:04:35,701
He'd answer using
that same dead, neutral,

1186
02:04:35,837 --> 02:04:38,067
technical language,

1187
02:04:39,374 --> 02:04:44,937
which makes him a truck driver,

1188
02:04:45,080 --> 02:04:48,743
an escorting officer,
an Unterführer,

1189
02:04:48,884 --> 02:04:55,050
a foreman, a scientist,
a technical director,

1190
02:04:55,190 --> 02:04:58,956
an Obersturmbannführer.

1191
02:05:06,234 --> 02:05:09,362
Were you the child at the window?

1192
02:05:23,485 --> 02:05:29,219
The child at the window was
Officer-Foreman Neumann's son.

1193
02:05:29,357 --> 02:05:31,757
He didn't want to tell me
his first name,

1194
02:05:31,893 --> 02:05:35,522
but I know "Arie" wasn't the one
his father gave him.

1195
02:07:06,521 --> 02:07:09,922
The musicians took their places

1196
02:07:10,058 --> 02:07:14,495
and I saw the scene from my dream.

1197
02:07:14,696 --> 02:07:19,861
Arie Neumann came in last,
holding his violin.

1198
02:07:20,769 --> 02:07:24,933
He remained standing,
looking directly at me.

1199
02:07:29,411 --> 02:07:35,043
I saw a man go towards the door
but I didn't shout for him to stop.

1200
02:07:36,117 --> 02:07:41,111
I saw the black mass
of tangled bodies.

1201
02:07:41,256 --> 02:07:43,087
Merchandise.

1202
02:07:45,160 --> 02:07:49,494
Cargo.

1203
02:07:51,433 --> 02:07:56,132
I saw a world of nakedness

1204
02:07:56,271 --> 02:07:59,729
under the yellowish,
caged-in light,

1205
02:07:59,875 --> 02:08:03,902
which slid down
a lightly sloping floor,

1206
02:08:04,045 --> 02:08:08,482
exposing a hand, a leg,

1207
02:08:08,617 --> 02:08:11,211
a crushed face,

1208
02:08:12,821 --> 02:08:15,312
a twisted mouth,

1209
02:08:15,457 --> 02:08:17,891
bleeding.

1210
02:08:18,526 --> 02:08:22,121
Fingers clutching
a dirty undergarment

1211
02:08:22,264 --> 02:08:31,866
stained with urine, vomit,
blood, sweat, drool.

1212
02:08:33,208 --> 02:08:35,335
Liquid.

1213
02:08:38,613 --> 02:08:41,309
Here was part of a back,

1214
02:08:41,449 --> 02:08:45,408
the head and arms
buried under other bodies.

1215
02:08:46,254 --> 02:08:50,850
There, a body entwined
around another.

1216
02:08:52,360 --> 02:08:55,090
And all these bodies....

1217
02:08:55,230 --> 02:08:56,822
Pieces.

1218
02:08:56,965 --> 02:08:59,160
Rolling over one another,

1219
02:08:59,301 --> 02:09:02,293
shifting the weight of the mass
towards the pit.

1220
02:09:02,437 --> 02:09:09,206
All these corpses, tangled up,
still muddled together,

1221
02:09:09,344 --> 02:09:14,247
but slowly separating from the mass
with the shifting weight.

1222
02:09:14,382 --> 02:09:16,850
Shifting weight.

1223
02:09:16,985 --> 02:09:21,388
Each one gradually pulling out
of the suffocating human embrace.

1224
02:09:21,523 --> 02:09:27,860
A grimacing face, turned blue,
stuporous.

1225
02:09:27,996 --> 02:09:30,123
And beneath....

1226
02:09:30,765 --> 02:09:33,256
The shit.

1227
02:09:33,401 --> 02:09:37,303
Little children cradled
in women's legs.

1228
02:09:37,439 --> 02:09:42,706
Scrawny old men,
little girls with sunken eyes,

1229
02:09:43,545 --> 02:09:47,743
naked boys covered in bruises.

1230
02:09:47,882 --> 02:09:50,282
All these creatures....

1231
02:09:50,418 --> 02:09:52,079
Pieces,

1232
02:09:52,220 --> 02:09:54,017
who had names.

1233
02:09:54,155 --> 02:09:56,214
Pieces.

1234
02:09:57,125 --> 02:09:58,092
Moïse.

1235
02:09:58,226 --> 02:09:59,750
Moshe.

1236
02:10:00,261 --> 02:10:02,126
My brother.

1237
02:10:02,864 --> 02:10:04,559
Robert.

1238
02:10:05,333 --> 02:10:07,233
My father.

1239
02:10:08,536 --> 02:10:10,128
Armand.

1240
02:10:10,905 --> 02:10:12,372
Miguel.

1241
02:10:14,576 --> 02:10:16,441
Amos.

1242
02:10:18,079 --> 02:10:20,070
Hannah.

1243
02:10:20,949 --> 02:10:22,849
Samuel.

1244
02:10:24,085 --> 02:10:26,212
Pieces.

1245
02:10:27,222 --> 02:10:28,849
My mother.

1246
02:10:30,425 --> 02:10:32,518
My love.

1247
02:10:33,828 --> 02:10:35,887
Pieces.

1248
02:10:36,464 --> 02:10:38,261
My sister.

1249
02:10:38,400 --> 02:10:39,492
Simone.

1250
02:10:39,634 --> 02:10:41,795
Magdalena.

1251
02:10:42,537 --> 02:10:47,770
Each of these bodies gradually
emerging from this vast naked sea

1252
02:10:47,909 --> 02:10:52,278
to fall one after the other,
in pairs, in bundles,

1253
02:10:52,414 --> 02:10:55,008
into the dark hole of the mine.

1254
02:10:55,150 --> 02:10:56,913
Darkness.

1255
02:10:57,052 --> 02:11:00,715
A sea of bodies, buried,
swallowed up.

